The new electoral laws require the electorate to present an identity card with a photograph and proof of American citizenship.
In addition, these laws reduce the period of early voting, abolish the right to register the electorate on the day of the expression of will, and remove the right to vote from citizens with a criminal record.
Before the 2006 elections, no American state had required voters to present an identity card with a photograph.
